(110,	0,	15,	20241218,	'ask',	'i wnat to move from portugal to australia',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2024-12-18 20:22:42',	0,	'2024-12-18 20:22:42',	0,	NULL),
(111,	110,	15,	20241218,	'reply',	'**Eligibility Requirements:**\n\n* **Skilled Occupation:** You must have a skill that is in high demand in Australia, as listed on the Skilled Occupation List (SOL).\n* **Age:** Generally, you must be under 45 years old.\n* **Education and Experience:** You must have relevant qualifications and work experience in your occupation.\n* **Language Proficiency:** You must have a competent level of English (IELTS 6 or PTE Academic 50).\n\n**Visa Options:**\n\n* **Skilled Independent Visa (Subclass 189):** For skilled workers with strong points based on their age, skills, and language proficiency.\n* **Skilled Nominated Visa (Subclass 190):** For skilled workers sponsored by an Australian state or territory government.\n* **Skilled Regional (Provisional) Visa (Subclass 491):** For skilled workers who want to live and work in regional Australia.\n\n**Steps to Apply:**\n\n1. **Skill Assessment:** Get your skills assessed by an approved Australian assessing authority to verify your eligibility.\n2. **EOI (Expression of Interest):** Submit an EOI to be placed in the SkillSelect pool. This will indicate your interest in migrating to Australia.\n3. **Invitation to Apply:** If your EOI is selected, you will receive an invitation to apply for the visa you are eligible for.\n4. **Visa Application:** Submit your visa application along with the required documents, including your skill assessment result.\n5. **Medical and Character Checks:** Undergo medical and character checks to meet Australian requirements.\n\n**Additional Information:**\n\n* **Points Test:** You will need to meet a certain number of points based on the factors mentioned above (age, skills, language, etc.).\n* **Skill Select Calculator:** Use the online calculator to assess your eligibility and estimate your points score.\n* **Agents:** You can engage the services of a registered migration agent to assist you with the process.\n* **Immigration Department Website:** Visit the website of the Australian Department of Home Affairs for detailed information and application forms.\n\n**Timeline:**\n\nThe processing time for visa applications can vary depending on the visa type and individual circumstances. However, it generally takes several months to receive a decision.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2024-12-18 20:22:42',	0,	'2024-12-18 20:22:42',	0,	NULL),
(112,	0,	15,	20241219,	'ask',	'what can you telme about the Wealthskey Migration',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2024-12-19 02:53:23',	0,	'2024-12-19 02:53:23',	0,	NULL),
(113,	112,	15,	20241219,	'reply',	'**Wealthskey Migration**\n\nWealthskey is a digital asset management and advisory platform. Its migration refers to the process of transferring user accounts and funds from the previous platform, known as Wealthskey 1.0, to the upgraded platform, Wealthskey 2.0.\n\n**Key Features:**\n\n* **Improved User Interface:** The new platform features a streamlined and intuitive user interface for easier navigation and account management.\n* **Enhanced Security:** Wealthskey 2.0 employs advanced security measures to protect user data and funds.\n* **Expanded Crypto Support:** The new platform supports a wider range of cryptocurrencies, providing users with greater investment options.\n* **Improved Portfolio Analysis:** Wealthskey 2.0 offers comprehensive portfolio analysis tools to help users monitor and optimize their investments.\n* **Tax Reporting Capabilities:** The platform provides automated tax reporting tools to streamline the tax filing process.\n\n**Timeline:**\n\nThe Wealthskey migration took place in phases throughout 2023. Users were given ample time to complete the migration process.\n\n**Benefits of Migrating:**\n\n* **Access to Improved Features:** Users can benefit from the enhanced features and services of Wealthskey 2.0.\n* **Enhanced Security:** The migration ensures that user accounts and funds remain securely protected.\n* **Streamlined Account Management:** The new platform simplifies account management and allows users to access their investments more conveniently.\n* **Automated Tax Reporting:** The tax reporting capabilities can save users time and effort during tax season.\n\n**Steps to Migrate:**\n\n* **Create a Wealthskey 2.0 Account:** If you do not have an account already, create one on the official Wealthskey website.\n* **Initiate Transfer:** Follow the instructions on the Wealthskey platform to initiate the account and fund transfer.\n* **Provide Verification:** Verify your identity and provide necessary information to complete the process.\n* **Monitor Progress:** Track the migration progress through the Wealthskey platform.\n\nOnce the migration is complete, users will have access to the full range of features and services available on Wealthskey 2.0. If you encounter any issues during the migration process, you can contact the Wealthskey support team for assistance.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2024-12-19 02:53:23',	0,	'2024-12-19 02:53:23',	0,	NULL),
(114,	0,	15,	20241220,	'ask',	'what about the Education and Schooling System in Portugal',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2024-12-20 01:49:23',	0,	'2024-12-20 01:49:23',	0,	NULL),
(115,	114,	15,	20241220,	'reply',	'**Education and Schooling System in Portugal**\n\n**Overview**\n\nThe Portuguese education system is decentralized and comprises four main levels: early childhood, basic education, secondary education, and higher education. It is compulsory and free for children between the ages of 6 and 18. The academic year runs from September to June.\n\n**Early Childhood Education (0-6 years)**\n\n* Pre-school (2-5 years): Voluntary and non-compulsory, provides a stimulating and developmentally appropriate environment.\n* Kindergarten (5-6 years): Mandatory and free, prepares children for primary school.\n\n**Basic Education (6-18 years)**\n\n**1st Cycle (6-10 years)**\n\n* Covers subjects such as Portuguese, Mathematics, Science, History, Geography, and Physical Education.\n* Students are assessed through continuous evaluation and final exams.\n\n**2nd Cycle (11-15 years)**\n\n* Students choose one of four streams: General, Scientific-Humanities, Science-Technology, and Arts.\n* Includes core subjects and a variety of elective courses.\n* Students are assessed through exams at the end of each year.\n\n**Secondary Education (15-18 years)**\n\n**3rd Cycle (16-18 years)**\n\n* Students choose one of three pathways: Academic (university preparation), Vocational (technical training), or Artistic.\n* Academic students take exams in a wide range of subjects.\n* Vocational students receive training in specific occupations.\n* Artistic students focus on developing their skills in the arts.\n\n**Higher Education**\n\n**Undergraduate Degrees (3-4 years)**\n\n* Bachelor&#039;s degrees offered in various fields, including Sciences, Social Sciences, Humanities, and Engineering.\n* Students must complete a research thesis or final project.\n\n**Master&#039;s Degrees (2 years)**\n\n* Advanced degrees that provide specialized knowledge and research skills.\n\n**Doctoral Degrees (3-4 years)**\n\n* Highest academic degree, involving original research and the completion of a dissertation.\n\n**Assessment and Evaluation**\n\n* Students are assessed through a combination of continuous evaluation and exams.\n* The Portuguese education system emphasizes formative assessment, providing students with feedback to improve their learning.\n\n**International Recognition**\n\n* Portuguese diplomas and degrees are recognized internationally.\n* The University of Lisbon and the University of Porto are among the top 500 universities in the world (QS World University Rankings 2022).\n\n**Challenges**\n\n* Educational disparities between urban and rural areas\n* High dropout rates in secondary education\n* Lack of investment in vocational education\n* Need for teachers with specialized expertise in STEM fields\n\n**Recent Reforms**\n\n* Reforms in 2023 aimed at:\n    * Reducing bureaucracy and administrative burdens\n    * Increasing teacher compensation\n    * Expanding access to early childhood education\n    * Promoting digital literacy and inclusivity',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2024-12-20 01:49:23',	0,	'2024-12-20 01:49:23',	0,	NULL),
(116,	0,	1,	20250219,	'ask',	'how can I apply for 186 visa?',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-02-19 13:12:24',	0,	'2025-02-19 13:12:24',	0,	NULL),
(117,	116,	1,	20250219,	'reply',	'**Eligibility Criteria for 186 Skilled Nominated Visa:**\n\n* You must have a skilled occupation on the SkillSelect Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL).\n* You must meet the points test with a minimum score of 65 points.\n* You must be invited to apply for a visa by an Australian state or territory government.\n* You must have a valid skills assessment from a relevant assessing authority.\n* You must meet the English language proficiency requirement.\n* You must have adequate health insurance.\n\n**Steps to Apply for an 186 Visa:**\n\n**1. Check if you are Eligible:**\n\n* Use the SkillSelect occupation finder to check if your occupation is on the MLTSSL.\n* Calculate your points using the Points Calculator.\n* Check if you have a valid skills assessment.\n\n**2. Get Invited by a State/Territory Government:**\n\n* Submit an Expression of Interest (EOI) through SkillSelect.\n* Wait for an invitation to apply for a visa from a state or territory government.\n\n**3. Gather Required Documents:**\n\n* Valid passport\n* Skills assessment\n* Evidence of meeting the points test\n* Proof of English language proficiency\n* Health insurance policy\n* Other supporting documents as required by the state/territory government\n\n**4. Lodge Your Visa Application:**\n\n* Complete the online visa application form (Form 186).\n* Attach all required documents.\n* Pay the visa application fee.\n\n**5. Biometrics and Medical Examination:**\n\n* Once your application is lodged, you may be required to provide biometrics and undergo a medical examination.\n\n**6. Visa Decision:**\n\n* The Department of Home Affairs will assess your application and make a decision.\n* You will be notified of the outcome in writing.\n\n**Additional Notes:**\n\n* You can apply for the 186 visa within or outside of Australia.\n* The processing time for the 186 visa can vary depending on the state/territory government&#039;s processing time and the complexity of your application.\n* If your visa is approved, you will be issued a visa grant letter and you will have 12 months to enter Australia and activate your visa.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-02-19 13:12:24',	0,	'2025-02-19 13:12:24',	0,	NULL),
(118,	0,	5,	20250424,	'ask',	'how can I apply for 482 visa?',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-04-24 15:10:05',	0,	'2025-04-24 15:10:05',	0,	NULL),
