(296,	0,	30,	20251007,	'ai',	'Okay, I can provide you with general information about the **Subclass 485 Temporary Graduate visa** for Australia.\n\n**Important Disclaimer:** I am an AI and this information is for general guidance only. Visa rules and requirements can change frequently. You **must always consult the official Australian Department of Home Affairs website (homeaffairs.gov.au)** or a registered migration agent for the most accurate, up-to-date, and personalized advice.\n\n---\n\n### Subclass 485 Temporary Graduate Visa (Australia)\n\nThe Subclass 485 visa is a temporary visa that allows international students who have recently graduated from an Australian educational institution to stay and work in Australia for a period after completing their studies. It\'s a pathway for graduates to gain work experience in Australia, and for some, a step towards permanent residency.\n\nThere are currently two main streams under the 485 visa:\n\n1.  **Graduate Work stream**\n2.  **Post-Study Work stream**\n\nThere were also a Second Post-Study Work stream, a Replacement stream, and a COVID-19 Pandemic event visa stream which had specific criteria, but the primary long-term streams are the first two. The eligibility and duration for these streams can vary.\n\n---\n\n#### ',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-07 11:48:06',	0,	'2025-10-07 11:48:06',	0,	NULL),
