(302,	0,	30,	20251007,	'ai',	'Okay, I can provide you with general information about the **Subclass 482 Temporary Skill Shortage (TSS) visa** for Australia.\n\n**Important Disclaimer:** As an AI, this information is for general guidance only. Visa rules and requirements can change frequently. You **must always consult the official Australian Department of Home Affairs website (homeaffairs.gov.au)** or a registered migration agent for the most accurate, up-to-date, and personalized advice.\n\n---\n\n### Subclass 482 Temporary Skill Shortage (TSS) Visa (Australia)\n\nThe Subclass 482 visa is a temporary visa that allows Australian employers to sponsor skilled overseas workers to fill nominated positions in their business when they can\'t find a suitably skilled Australian citizen or permanent resident to do the work.\n\nIt\'s primarily an employer-sponsored visa and has three main streams:\n\n1.  **Short-term stream:** For occupations on the Short-term Skilled Occupation List (STSOL).\n2.  **Medium-term stream:** For occupations on the Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL) or a Regional Occupation List.\n3.  **Labour Agreement stream:** For employers who have a formal Labour Agreement with the Australian government.\n\n---\n\n#### Key Features and Requirements (General):\n\n**For the Employer (Sponsor):**\n\n*   **Standard Business Sponsorship (SBS):** The employer must be approved as a standard business sponsor. This involves demonstrating that the business is lawfully operating, has a good training record (or an exemption applies), and meets other sponsorship obligations.\n*   **Nomination:** The employer must nominate an eligible skilled position within their business. This involves:\n    *   Demonstrating a genuine need for an overseas worker.\n    *   Showing that they have tried to recruit an Australian worker (Labour Market Testing - LMT) unless an exemption applies.\n    *   Ensuring the position\'s terms and conditions are no less favourable than those for an Australian worker.\n    *   Paying the Skilling Australians Fund (SAF) levy.\n*   **Occupation List:** The nominated occupation must be on the relevant skilled occupation list (STSOL or MLTSSL) for the chosen stream, unless a Labour Agreement applies.\n\n**For the Visa Applicant (Employee):**\n\n*   **Nominated Occupation:** You must be nominated for an eligible occupation by an approved sponsor.\n*   **Skills Assessment:** You',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-07 12:09:27',	0,	'2025-10-07 12:09:27',	0,	NULL),
