(316,	0,	30,	20251007,	'ai',	'Okay, I understand. Here\'s a concise summary of the **Subclass 500 Student visa** for Australia.\n\n---\n\n### Subclass 500 Student Visa (Australia) - Concise Summary\n\nThis visa allows international students to study a full-time, registered course in Australia.\n\n**Key Eligibility Requirements:**\n\n*   **Enrolment:** Must be enrolled in a full-time course registered on CRICOS (provide eCoE).\n*   **Genuine Temporary Entrant (GTE):** Must prove you intend to come to Australia temporarily for study.\n*   **Financial Capacity:** Must have sufficient funds for tuition, living costs, and travel.\n*   **English Language:** Meet specified English proficiency requirements (unless exempt).\n*   **Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC):** Must have valid health insurance for the entire stay.\n*   **Health & Character:** Meet Australia\'s health and character requirements.\n*   **Age:** Generally must be 6 years old or older.\n\n**Key Features:**\n\n*   **Work Rights:** Can work up to 40 hours per fortnight while your course is in session, and full-time during scheduled breaks. (Check current temporary changes).\n*   **Duration:** Granted for the duration of your course, plus a short stay period afterwards.\n*   **Family:** Eligible family members (spouse/partner, dependent children) can be included in the application.\n\n**Application Process (General Steps):**\n\n1.  **Get Accepted:** Obtain a Confirmation of Enrolment (eCoE) from a CRICOS-registered institution.\n2.  **Gather Documents:** Prepare all required documents (passport, GTE statement, financial proof, OSHC, English test, etc.).\n3.  **Apply Online:** Lodge the visa application through the Department of Home Affairs ImmiAccount.\n4.  **Attend Biometrics/Health Checks:** If requested.\n5.  **Decision:** Await the visa outcome.\n\n**Cost:** The base application charge is typically AUD $710 (as of early 2024), with additional charges for family members.\n\n**Important Note:** Visa rules can change. Always verify information on the official Department of Home Affairs website (homeaffairs.gov.au).',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-07 13:16:40',	0,	'2025-10-07 13:16:40',	0,	NULL),
