(324,	0,	30,	20251007,	'ai',	'I understand you\'re wondering if you\'re eligible for the Subclass 186 visa. To give you an initial idea, I need a bit more information about your situation.\n\nThe Subclass 186 visa has specific requirements for the applicant (you) and the nominating employer.\n\nCould you please provide the following details so I can better assess your potential eligibility?\n\nRegarding You (the potential visa applicant):\n\n1.  Age: How old are you? (The general age limit is under 45, with some exemptions).\n2.  Occupation: What is your exact occupation or job title?\n3.  Qualifications: What are your highest qualifications (e.g., Bachelor\'s Degree, Master\'s, Diploma) and in what field?\n4.  Work Experience: How many years of full-time, relevant work experience do you have in your nominated occupation? (The requirements vary by stream).\n5.  English Language: Do you have results from an English language test (e.g., IELTS, PTE, TOEFL iBT) and what were your scores? (e.g., IELTS 6.0 in each band, or equivalent).\n6.  Current Visa Status (if in Australia): If you are currently in Australia, what visa do you hold? (e.g., 482 TSS visa, 457 visa, Student visa, etc.)\n7.  Skills Assessment: Have you undergone a formal skills assessment for your occupation by the relevant Australian assessing authority? If so, which authority and what was the outcome? (Required for Direct Entry stream).\n8.  Nationality: What is your country of citizenship?\n\nRegarding a Potential Employer (if you have one):\n\n9.  Employer Name/Industry: Do you have an Australian employer who is willing to sponsor you, or are you looking for one? What industry are they in?\n10. Previous Employer Sponsorship: Have you previously worked for an Australian employer on a temporary skilled visa (like a 457 or 482 visa)? If so, for how long and in what role?\n\nOnce I have this information, I can give you a more tailored assessment of which 186 stream (Temporary Residence Transition, Direct Entry, or Labour Agreement) might be relevant to you and what your chances look like.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-07 14:27:41',	0,	'2025-10-07 14:27:41',	0,	NULL),
