(341,	0,	30,	20251008,	'ask',	'do you know 485 visa',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-08 08:22:23',	0,	'2025-10-08 08:22:23',	0,	NULL),
(342,	0,	30,	20251008,	'reply',	'Yes, absolutely! I am very familiar with the Subclass 485 Temporary Graduate visa for Australia.\n\nThis is a crucial visa for many international students who have completed their studies in Australia and wish to stay and gain work experience, or even pursue further migration pathways.\n\nLet me provide you with a detailed overview:\n\nSubclass 485 Temporary Graduate Visa (Australia)\n\nThe Subclass 485 visa allows eligible international students to remain in Australia temporarily after they have completed their studies. It provides an opportunity to gain valuable Australian work experience, which can be beneficial for future permanent residency applications.\n\nThere are generally three streams, each with specific eligibility criteria and duration:\n\n1.  Graduate Work Stream\n2.  Post-Study Work Stream\n3.  Replacement Stream (introduced due to COVID-19 travel restrictions)\n4.  Second Post-Study Work Stream (an extension for those meeting specific criteria)\n\nGeneral Eligibility Requirements for all 485 Streams:\n\n   Age: You must be under 50 years of age when you apply.\n   Eligible Visa: You must hold an eligible visa (usually a student visa, or a Bridging A or Bridging B visa granted after applying for an eligible visa) at the time of application.\n   Australian Study Requirement: You must have completed an eligible qualification in Australia in the last 6 months. This generally means:\n       Your course was registered on CRICOS.\n       You studied for at least 16 calendar months.\n       You completed at least 2 academic years (92 weeks) of study.\n       You completed your studies while holding an Australian student visa.\n   English Language Proficiency: You must demonstrate \"Competent English\" at the time of application. This generally means:\n       IELTS: 6.0 overall with no band less than 5.0 (or 6.5 overall with no band less than 5.5 for applications lodged on or after 11 December 2023)\n       PTE Academic: 50 overall with no communicative skill less than 36 (or 56 overall with no communicative skill less than 42 for applications lodged on or after 11 December 2023)\n       TOEFL iBT, OET, Cambridge C1 Advanced (CAE) are also accepted with equivalent scores.\n   Health Insurance: You must have adequate health insurance for the entire duration of your stay in Australia.\n   Health and Character: You and any family members included in your application must meet Australia\'s health and character requirements.\n   First 485 Visa: Generally, you can only be granted a 485 visa (Post-Study Work stream) once, unless you are eligible for the Second Post-Study Work stream or the Replacement stream.\n\nSpecific Requirements and Duration by Stream:\n\n1. Graduate Work Stream\n\n   Purpose: For international students who complete an eligible qualification and whose skills are in demand in Australia.\n   Qualification: Your qualification must be closely related to an occupation on the Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL).\n   Skills Assessment: You must have a positive skills assessment for your nominated occupation from the relevant Australian assessing authority.\n   Duration: Typically 18-24 months.\n       Note: Certain passport holders (e.g., Hong Kong and British National Overseas passport holders) may be granted a visa for up to 5 years.\n\n2. Post-Study Work Stream\n\n   Purpose: For international students who have completed a higher education degree (Bachelor\'s, Master\'s, or PhD) from an Australian education provider.\n   Qualification: You must have completed a Bachelor\'s degree or higher. No specific occupation list or skills assessment is required.\n   Duration: The visa length depends on your highest completed Australian qualification:\n       Bachelor\'s Degree: 2 years\n       Master\'s by Coursework: 2 years\n       Master\'s by Research: 3 years\n       Doctoral Degree (PhD): 4 years\n       Extensions:\n           Regional Study: An additional 1-2 years may be granted if you completed your degree at a regional campus and continue to live and work in a regional area.\n           Selected Degrees: An additional 2 years may be granted for graduates of specific degrees identified as areas of verified labour shortage (e.g., certain health, engineering, IT, teaching qualifications). This is a recent update to address skill shortages.\n           Indian Citizens: Under the Australia-India Economic Cooperation and Trade Agreement (ECTA), eligible Indian graduates can receive longer visas:\n               Bachelor\'s: 2-3 years\n               Master\'s: 3-5 years\n               PhD: 4-6 years (depending on the degree and specific conditions).\n\n3. Replacement Stream\n\n   Purpose: For former Subclass 485 visa holders whose visas expired or were about to expire due to COVID-19 travel restrictions.\n   Eligibility: You must have held a 485 visa (either stream) that was granted on or before 15 December 2021 and expired on or after 1 February 2020. You must also be outside Australia for a period between 1 February 2020 and 14 December 2021.\n   Duration: Generally the same duration as your original 485 visa.\n\n4. Second Post-Study Work Stream\n\n   Purpose: An option for those who have already held a first Post-Study Work stream visa.\n   Eligibility: You must have graduated from an eligible education provider in a designated regional area and subsequently resided and worked in a specified regional area for at least two years while holding your first 485 visa.\n   *',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-08 08:22:23',	0,	'2025-10-08 08:22:23',	0,	NULL),
