(392,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Hello! As an AI, I don\'t experience feelings or states of being like humans do, but I am fully operational and ready to assist you with your migration and visa inquiries for Australia, the UK, Canada, or the USA.\n\nHow can I help you today? Do you have any further questions about studying in Australia, visa pathways, or anything else?',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:01:20',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:01:20',	0,	NULL),
(393,	0,	30,	20251009,	'ask',	'short instrument of 186visa',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:02:20',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:02:20',	0,	NULL),
(394,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Okay, here\'s a short summary of the Australian Subclass 186 (Employer Nomination Scheme - ENS) visa:\n\nThe Subclass 186 visa is a permanent resident visa for skilled workers who are nominated by an Australian employer.\n\nKey points:\n\n   Purpose: Allows Australian employers to sponsor skilled workers for permanent residency to fill ongoing skilled positions.\n   Sponsorship: Requires an approved Australian employer to nominate you for a skilled occupation.\n   Streams: Primarily has two streams:\n       Direct Entry Stream: For those who don\'t qualify for the Temporary Residence Transition stream, requiring a positive skill assessment and usually 3 years of relevant work experience.\n       Temporary Residence Transition (TRT) Stream: For Subclass 482 (TSS) visa holders who have worked for their nominating employer for a specified period (usually 2-3 years) in the nominated occupation.\n   Permanent Residency: It is a direct pathway to Australian permanent residency from the outset.\n   Age Limit: Generally, applicants must be under 45 years of age at the time of application, though some exemptions apply.\n   English: Requires competent English (e.g., IELTS 6.0 in each band, or equivalent).\n*   Family: You can include your family members (partner and dependent children) in your application.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:02:20',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:02:20',	0,	NULL),
(395,	0,	30,	20251009,	'ask',	'short summary of 500 visa',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:07:37',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:07:37',	0,	NULL),
(396,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Okay, here\'s a short summary of the Australian Subclass 500 (Student) visa:\n\nThe Subclass 500 visa allows international students to come to Australia to study a full-time, registered course at an eligible Australian education provider.\n\nKey points:\n\n   Purpose: To study a CRICOS-registered course in Australia.\n   Enrolment: Requires a Confirmation of Enrolment (CoE) from an Australian education provider.\n   Genuine Temporary Entrant (GTE): Applicants must demonstrate a genuine intention to stay in Australia temporarily for study purposes.\n   Financial Capacity: You must show evidence of sufficient funds to cover tuition, living costs, and travel.\n   English Language: Generally requires meeting English proficiency requirements (e.g., IELTS, TOEFL, PTE scores).\n   Duration: Granted for the duration of your course, plus a short stay period afterwards.\n   Work Rights: Allows limited work rights (generally 48 hours per fortnight during study, full-time during breaks).\n   Family: You can include eligible family members (partner and dependent children) in your application.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:07:37',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:07:37',	0,	NULL),
(397,	0,	30,	20251009,	'ask',	'short summary of 485visa',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:39',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:39',	0,	NULL),
(398,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Okay, here\'s a short summary of the Australian Subclass 485 (Temporary Graduate) visa:\n\nThe Subclass 485 visa allows eligible international students who have recently graduated from an Australian education institution to stay and work in Australia temporarily after completing their studies.\n\nKey points:\n\n   Purpose: To gain work experience in Australia, often used as a pathway to skilled migration.\n   Streams: Primarily two streams:\n       Graduate Work Stream: For graduates with specific qualifications (e.g., VET, bachelor\'s, master\'s, PhD) in an occupation on the skilled occupation list, requiring a skill assessment. Typically granted for 18 months.\n       Post-Study Work Stream: For graduates with a bachelor\'s degree or higher from an Australian institution, regardless of their field of study. Duration varies from 2 to 4 years, depending on the qualification and sometimes the study location (e.g., regional areas may offer extensions).\n   Eligibility: Must be under 50 years old, hold an eligible qualification from an Australian institution, meet the Australian Study Requirement, and apply within a specific period after graduation.\n   English: Requires competent English (e.g., IELTS 6.0 overall with no band less than 5.0, or equivalent).\n   Work Rights: Full-time work rights.\n   Path to PR: Provides an opportunity to gain Australian work experience, improve English, or prepare for other skilled migration (permanent residency) visas.\n*   Family: You can include eligible family members (partner and dependent children) in your application.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:39',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:39',	0,	NULL),
(399,	0,	30,	20251009,	'ask',	'really?',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:57',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:57',	0,	NULL),
(400,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Yes, absolutely! The information I provided about the Australian Subclass 485 (Temporary Graduate) visa is accurate based on the current regulations from the Department of Home Affairs.\n\nIt\'s a very popular and crucial visa for many international students looking to gain post-study work experience in Australia and often serves as a stepping stone towards permanent residency.\n\nDo you have any specific aspects of the 485 visa you\'d like me to elaborate on, or perhaps compare it with another visa?',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:57',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:11:57',	0,	NULL),
