(426,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Okay, I understand you might not know exactly where to start, and that\'s perfectly fine! Many people feel that way when exploring international study and migration options.\n\nLet me help by suggesting some common starting points. Perhaps you can tell me a little bit about what you\'re generally hoping to achieve, or what\'s on your mind?\n\nFor example, you could tell me:\n\n   What are your study goals? Are you looking for undergraduate (Bachelor\'s), postgraduate (Master\'s/PhD), or vocational studies?\n   What field of study are you interested in? (e.g., Engineering, Business, IT, Health, Arts, etc.)\n   What is your highest level of education so far?\n   Do you have any work experience? If so, in what field?\n   Are you looking for a country that offers good post-study work opportunities, or even a pathway to permanent residency after graduation?\n   Do you have a preferred country in mind, or are you open to suggestions for Australia, the UK, Canada, or the USA?\n*   What\'s important to you in a university or a new country? (e.g., cost, climate, specific city, university ranking, cultural diversity, safety)\n\nEven just a few words from any of these points can help me guide you towards the most relevant information. Don\'t worry about having a perfect answer – just tell me what comes to mind!',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 01:21:38',	0,	'2025-10-09 01:21:38',	0,	NULL),
