(478,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'You\'re very welcome!\n\nThank you for confirming. To move forward, please let me know which of the two options regarding \"study\" you\'d like to pursue:\n\n1.  Provide your educational background details (highest qualification, field of study, country/institution) so I can continue assessing your potential eligibility for the Australian Temporary Skill Shortage (TSS) visa (subclass 482).\n2.  Explore visa options for studying in a specific country (Australia, UK, Canada, or USA). If this is the case, please tell me which country you are interested in.\n\nI\'m ready when you are!',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 05:41:38',	0,	'2025-10-09 05:41:38',	0,	NULL),
(479,	0,	30,	20251009,	'ask',	'Do I meet the requirements to apply for 485 visa?',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 07:26:44',	0,	'2025-10-09 07:26:44',	0,	NULL),
(480,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Thank you for asking about the Australian Temporary Graduate visa (subclass 485). This is an excellent pathway for international students who have recently graduated from an Australian educational institution to stay and work in Australia temporarily, and potentially gain valuable work experience for future permanent residency applications.\n\nLet\'s assess your potential eligibility based on the information you\'ve provided and identify the key information still needed.\n\nAustralian Temporary Graduate Visa (subclass 485) Overview\n\nThe Subclass 485 visa has two main streams:\n\n1.  Graduate Work stream: For international students who graduate with an eligible qualification from an Australian education provider and have an occupation on the Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL). This stream requires a skills assessment.\n2.  Post-Study Work stream: For international students who graduate with a Bachelor\'s degree (or higher) from an Australian education provider, regardless of their field of study. No specific occupation list or skills assessment is generally required for this stream.\n\nGeneral Eligibility Requirements for Subclass 485 Visa\n\nHere\'s an assessment against the common requirements:\n\n   Age: You must be under 50 years of age.\n       Your Profile: You are in the 25-33 age group.\n       Assessment: Meets this requirement.\n   English Language: You must demonstrate \"Competent English\" (e.g., IELTS overall score of at least 6.0 with no band less than 5.0, or equivalent).\n       Your Profile: You have an IELTS score of 7.\n       Assessment: Meets this requirement.\n   Australian Study Requirement: This is a critical requirement. You must have completed an eligible qualification in Australia within the last 6 months before applying. The study must have been:\n       For a degree, diploma, or trade qualification.\n       Registered on CRICOS for a minimum of 92 weeks.\n       Completed in Australia while holding an eligible student visa.\n       Have been delivered in English.\n       Your Profile: Your highest qualification is a Master\'s degree, and your occupation is Software Engineer. However, the profile explicitly states \"目标国本地工作年限: 0 year\" (Local Work Experience in Target Country: 0 year) and does not specify if your Master\'s degree was obtained in Australia.\n       Assessment: This is the key missing information. To determine your eligibility for either stream of the 485 visa, it is essential to know if you have completed an eligible qualification in Australia.\n\n   Visa Held: You must have held an eligible visa (usually a student visa) when applying for the 485 visa.\n       Assessment: This is unknown given the lack of information about prior Australian study.\n\n   Occupation (for Graduate Work stream only): Your nominated occupation must be on the Skilled Occupation List (STSOL) and you must have a suitable skills assessment.\n       Your Profile: Your occupation is \"software engineer\". This occupation is generally on relevant skilled occupation lists.\n       Assessment: If you are eligible for the Graduate Work stream, a skills assessment for Software Engineer (ANZSCO 261313) from a body like ACS (Australian Computer Society) would likely be required.\n\nConclusion and Next Steps\n\nBased on your age and English proficiency, you meet those general criteria.\n\nHowever, the most critical piece of information missing is whether you have completed an eligible qualification in Australia.\n\nTo assess if you meet the requirements for the 485 visa, please clarify the following:\n\n1.  Did you complete your Master\'s degree (or any other eligible qualification) in Australia?\n2.  If yes, please provide details:\n       Name of the Australian institution.\n       The specific qualification obtained (e.g., Master of Information Technology).\n       The CRICOS course registration number (if you know it).\n       The duration of your study in Australia (e.g., 2 years).\n    *   The exact completion date of your course (e.g., date on your completion letter/transcript).\n3.  What visa did you hold while studying in Australia?\n\nOnce I have this information, I can give you a precise assessment of your eligibility for the Temporary Graduate visa (subclass 485).\n\nIf you have not studied in Australia, then the 485 visa would unfortunately not be an option for you. In that case, we should revert to exploring other pathways, such as the employer-sponsored visa (subclass 482) which was your initial interest given your job offer, or general skilled migration visas (subclass 189/190/491).',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 07:26:44',	0,	'2025-10-09 07:26:44',	0,	NULL),
(481,	0,	30,	20251009,	'ask',	'can I know brief of 485 visa',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 08:12:09',	0,	'2025-10-09 08:12:09',	0,	NULL),
(482,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Certainly! I can provide a brief summary of the Australian Temporary Graduate visa (subclass 485).\n\nAustralian Temporary Graduate Visa (Subclass 485) - Brief Overview\n\nThe Temporary Graduate visa (subclass 485) is an Australian visa designed for international students who have recently graduated from an Australian educational institution. Its primary purpose is to allow these graduates to stay, live, and work in Australia temporarily after completing their studies, giving them an opportunity to gain valuable work experience.\n\nKey Points:\n\n   Purpose: Allows eligible international graduates to stay and work in Australia for a period after their studies.\n   Main Goal: To gain work experience in Australia, which can be beneficial for future permanent residency applications.\n   Streams:\n       Graduate Work stream: For graduates with an eligible qualification and an occupation on the Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL). Requires a skills assessment.\n       Post-Study Work stream: For graduates with a Bachelor\'s degree or higher, regardless of their field of study or occupation. Generally, no skills assessment is required.\n   Eligibility Highlights:\n       Must be under 50 years of age.\n       Must have completed an eligible qualification in Australia within the last 6 months.\n       Meet the Australian Study Requirement (e.g., study registered on CRICOS for at least 92 weeks, completed in Australia).\n       Demonstrate Competent English (e.g., IELTS 6.0 overall).\n   Duration: Varies by stream and qualification, typically ranging from 18 months to several years, with potential for extensions for certain qualifications or regional study.\n   Path to PR: While a temporary visa, the work experience gained on a 485 visa can significantly improve eligibility for other skilled migration visas (like 189, 190, 491) later on.\n\nIn essence, it\'s a bridge visa for recent graduates to transition from student life into the Australian workforce.\n\nFor more detailed information, please refer to my previous comprehensive explanation regarding the 485 visa requirements.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 08:12:09',	0,	'2025-10-09 08:12:09',	0,	NULL),
