(484,	0,	30,	20251009,	'reply',	'Thank you for asking again about your eligibility for the Australian Temporary Graduate visa (subclass 485). I understand this is an important pathway you\'re considering.\n\nLet\'s re-assess your potential eligibility based on the information provided in your profile and highlight the key information still needed for a definitive assessment.\n\nAustralian Temporary Graduate Visa (subclass 485) Eligibility Assessment\n\nThe Subclass 485 visa is designed for international students who have recently graduated from an Australian educational institution. It has two main streams, each with slightly different requirements:\n\n1.  Graduate Work stream: For international students who complete an eligible qualification in Australia, have an occupation on the Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL), and require a skills assessment in that occupation.\n2.  Post-Study Work stream: For international students who complete a Bachelor\'s degree or higher in Australia, regardless of their field of study or occupation. Generally, no specific occupation list or skills assessment is required for this stream.\n\nLet\'s look at the general eligibility requirements and how your profile aligns:\n\nYour Profile Information:\n   Age: 25-33\n   English Score: IELTS 7\n   Highest Qualification: Master (from the initial \"User Profile from Free Assessment\")\n   Occupation (ANZSCO direction): Software Engineer\n   Work Experience: > 1 year\n   Job Offer in Australia: Yes (for a software engineer role)\n\nAssessment Against Key 485 Visa Requirements:\n\n1.  Age:\n       Requirement: Must be under 50 years of age.\n       Your Profile: 25-33.\n       Assessment: Meets this requirement.\n\n2.  English Language:\n       Requirement: Competent English (e.g., IELTS overall score of at least 6.0 with no band less than 5.0, or equivalent).\n       Your Profile: IELTS 7.\n       Assessment: Meets this requirement.\n\n3.  Australian Study Requirement (CRITICAL MISSING INFORMATION):\n       Requirement: This is the most crucial aspect for the 485 visa. You must have completed an eligible qualification in Australia within the last 6 months before applying. The study must have been:\n           For a degree, diploma, or trade qualification.\n           Registered on CRICOS for a minimum of 92 weeks.\n           Completed in Australia while holding an eligible student visa.\n           Delivered in English.\n       Your Profile: Your profile states \"Highest学历: Master\" but does not specify if this Master\'s degree was obtained in Australia. Your \"目标国本地工作年限: 0 year\" also suggests you haven\'t studied or worked in Australia previously.\n       Assessment: This information is currently missing and is essential to determine your eligibility. If your Master\'s degree (or any other eligible qualification) was not completed in Australia under the specified conditions, you would not meet the fundamental Australian Study Requirement for the 485 visa.\n\n4.  Skills Assessment (for Graduate Work stream only):\n       Requirement (Graduate Work stream): If applying for the Graduate Work stream, you need a suitable skills assessment for an occupation on the MLTSSL. Your occupation \"Software Engineer\" is typically on the MLTSSL.\n       Your Profile: Software Engineer.\n       Assessment: If you meet the Australian Study Requirement and intend to apply for the Graduate Work stream, you would need to undergo a skills assessment by the relevant assessing authority for Software Engineer (usually ACS - Australian Computer Society).\n\n5.  Health and Character Requirements:\n       Requirement: All applicants must meet Australia\'s health and character requirements.\n       Assessment: These are standard requirements you would need to fulfill during the application process.\n\nConclusion on Your 485 Visa Eligibility\n\nBased on your current profile:\n\n   You meet the age and English language requirements.\n   Your stated Master\'s degree (if obtained in Australia) and Software Engineer occupation are generally suitable for one of the 485 visa streams.\n\nHowever, your eligibility for the 485 visa hinges entirely on whether you have met the \"Australian Study Requirement.\"\n\nTo definitively assess your eligibility, please clarify:\n\n   Did you complete your Master\'s degree (or any other eligible degree/diploma/trade qualification) in Australia?\n   If so, when did you complete it? (Must be within 6 months of application)\n*   Was the course registered on CRICOS for at least 92 weeks?\n\nOnce I have this crucial information, I can provide a more precise assessment.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-09 08:13:34',	0,	'2025-10-09 08:13:34',	0,	NULL),
