(514,	0,	30,	20251010,	'reply',	'Yes, based on the information you\'ve provided, you appear to have a strong potential to be eligible for the Australian Temporary Skill Shortage (TSS) visa (subclass 482).\n\nHere\'s why:\n\n1.  Occupation & Job Offer: You have a job offer as a Software Engineer (ANZSCO 261313), which is on Australia\'s Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL). This makes you eligible for the Medium-Term stream of the 482 visa, allowing for a visa duration of up to four years.\n2.  Employer Sponsorship: Your employer in Australia must be an approved Standard Business Sponsor and must nominate your position. With a job offer, this step is typically initiated by your prospective employer.\n3.  English Language: Your IELTS score of 7 is well above the minimum requirement for the 482 visa Medium-Term stream (IELTS 5 overall, with a minimum of 4.5 in each component), fulfilling this crucial criteria.\n4.  Skills and Experience: Your Master\'s degree and over 1 year of work experience are generally sufficient. While a formal skills assessment from a relevant authority like the Australian Computer Society (ACS) is usually required for permanent visas (like 186 or 189/190), it may also be requested for the 482 visa depending on your specific circumstances and the nominating employer.\n\nKey Information to Supplement:\nTo proceed with a 482 visa application, your employer will need to lodge a \'Nomination\' application for your position, and you will then lodge your \'Visa\' application. You\'ll need to gather evidence of your qualifications and work experience, and potentially obtain a skills assessment if requested by the Department of Home Affairs.',	'immigration',	1,	0,	'2025-10-10 01:05:49',	0,	'2025-10-10 01:05:49',	0,	NULL);
